dialog.text: Oh good. There you are. Let's get this over with. I've got loans to foreclose.
Um.... Erm.. Who are you?
I'm Ebenezer Scrooge. Why don't you already know that?
Sorry, I'm new here. This is my first assignment.
Hrump. No surprise that heaven would send me a trainee. You guys don't run a very tight ship up there.
So what are we supposed to do now?
Jeez. Do I have to do everything around here?
Look. You are the Ghost of Christmas Present. Though you don't look very Christmasy. You look kinda fowl, actually.
Yes, we had a few mixups in Heaven.
No kidding. Anyway, You are supposed to show me scenes of joy and misery to make me soften my heart.
And I'll pretend to be softened until you leave me alone.  Got it?
I guess so.  So how do I do that?
Well, the previous guy left his notebook on the table over there. Maybe there's something in it.
Scrooge's un-filmed action movie script:  Like The Dickens: A Christmas Peril
It seems to be about three evil ghosts who torment a good business man until he gets his revenge.
Handbook for Holiday Spirits and Cocktails
Oh, this looks useful.
Well, what does it say chicken head?
It says the Handbook for Holiday Spirits and Cocktails.
I suppose I am a "holiday spirit".
And you do have a cocktail!
Chapter 5: Remembrance
The key to a successful heart melting is to show the client scenes of people close to him who can provide heart warming warmth.
Hmm.  People close to me. I ain't got any of those.
Well, surely you must have some relatives?
Just my nephew Fred. Every year he invites me to his stupid party with figgy pudding. Humbug! Nonsense!
Well, let's go see them just in case. The book says we can fly.
Fine, but I'm not flying anywhere without my robe. Its chilly out. Go find it. It's probably in my bedroom somewhere. Here's the key.
Robe acquired
Blast, you found it. I must find better hiding places for my things.
Well I'm still not going without my rubber ducky.
You sure are picky.
They don't call me Scrooge for nothin'.
If I find your rubber ducky you'll go?
Yes, I'll go.
But I won't be happy about it.
Found Duck
Okay, let's go.
I'm not going anywhere.
But you said you'd go if I found the rubber ducky.
I said you had to find *my* rubber ducky. That duck isn't mine.
Why is someone else's rubber ducky in your house?
How should I know?!
Now go find my duck or I'm stayin' put.
Duck found
Blast, you found it. And I had hidden it so well.
Fine. I'll go, but let’s be quick about it.
At last, now we can visit your Nephew Fred's annual Christmas party. Which way out?
You're supposed to fly, so I assume out a window or some nonsense.
We have returned to your house. Do you feel like mending your ways now?
All I've learned is that everyone is better off when I'm mean. And that I hate jalpenos.
My heart remains firmly frozen.
Alas I've tried everything I know.
Then be off with you!
Christmas greetings gentlemen!
Who are you?
Why I'm the ghost of Christmas Suture, of course
Christmas *Suture* ?
Yeah, that transmogrification guy is a lousy speller.
Anyway, I'll take over from here. You can head out the window.
Thanks, and good luck. You're gonna need it.
todo list
* add spikes to prevent late night chimney intruders
* bury food scraps before adorable street urchins can find them
* foreclose orphange
* return DVD rentals
Who do you think you are, Santa Claus?
Who do you think you are? Santa Claus?!
Didn't your mother ever teach you not to open other peoples' presents?
Hey, do you know how to get to the reindeer games? I'm late for practice.
